{"word":"προέχω","slug":"προέχω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>προέχω</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πρό\">πρό</a>, <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἔχω\">ἔχω</a></el>] a verb with complex history; in <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ NT\">NT</a> only <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ intr.\">intr.</a> in the sense <b>surpass/excel</b> and in the form <el>προέχομαι</el>, which is to be taken as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pass.\">pass.</a> within the context of <b><a href='B:520 3:9'>Ro 3:9</a></b> in the sense are we losing our advantage? <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:προευαγγελίζομαι\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:προήγαγον\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}